# Fluff Date: 2026-02-26 19:50:04
<overview>
<p>The Texas-class battleship defined Star League naval power for nearly two centuries. Commissioned in 2618 after the Hegemony's aging Monsoon-class battleships proved consistently outmatched by member state navies, the Texas represented a quantum leap in capital warship design. Krester Ship Construction, already celebrated for the agile Kimagure-class pursuit cruiser, answered the SLDF's demand for a battleship combining devastating firepower with extraordinary maneuverability for its class. The revolutionary Panthex lamellor ferro-carbide armor proved central to achieving this vision -- nearly 1,800 tons of the advanced composite provided protection equivalent to 4,500 tons of conventional plating, freeing enormous mass for the engines and weapons that gave the Texas performance no previous battleship could approach. Fifty-two were constructed at Krester's sprawling Terra orbital yards, including the famed Station Alpha complex, and the class served as the capital backbone of every major SLDF fleet for over a century. The Amaris Civil War destroyed the vast majority, but the Texas holds the singular distinction of being the only Inner Sphere battleship class to survive into the Clan era, where surviving vessels served as treasured flagships for centuries -- the ultimate prizes of the Exodus fleet.</p>
</overview>

<capabilities>
<p>Displacing 1,560,000 tons across 1,209 meters of Galadin SYN hull structure, the Texas employs a radical broadside-dominant weapons philosophy unique among Star League capital ships. The vessel mounts no weapons whatsoever in its nose or direct aft arcs, instead concentrating devastating firepower along its flanks to deliver crushing broadsides in the classic naval tradition. Each forward quarter mounts four Heavy Naval PPCs, two Killer Whale capital missile launchers, and a NAC/40 super-heavy naval autocannon for close-range engagements. The broadsides each carry twelve NL45 naval lasers and two AR10 flexible missile launchers loaded with mixed Barracuda and White Shark missiles, creating walls of energy and warhead fire along the beam. The aft quarters mirror the broadsides' laser and missile batteries while adding four more Heavy Naval PPCs per side, giving the Texas sixteen Heavy NPPCs and forty-eight NL45s total -- an enormous energy weapons suite managed by 2,825 double heat sinks generating 5,650 points of effective dissipation. Nearly 1,800 tons of Panthex lamellor ferro-carbide armor provides protection equivalent to 4,500 tons of standard plating, giving the Texas defensive resilience normally associated with vessels far above its mass. Three gravity decks, six docking collars, and bays for forty aerospace fighters and sixteen small craft support the crew of 862 in extended independent deployments. The Clan refit introduced around 2835 added lithium-fusion batteries for rapid successive jumps and a mobile HPG for independent communications, reducing armor slightly and trading approximately 15,000 tons of cargo capacity for these strategic systems.</p>
</capabilities>

<deployment>
<p>The five Texas-class battleships that survived the Exodus Civil War became the most prestigious command vessels in the Clan fleet after receiving comprehensive refits around 2835. The SLS Prinz Eugen gained immediate infamy for the mutiny of August 2785, when nine ships attempted to return to the Inner Sphere before being brutally suppressed. Decommissioned as a prison ship orbiting Strana Mechty, the Prinz Eugen was later subverted by the Society and transferred to the reborn Clan Burrock, only to be destroyed at Tanis in 3073 by a Clan Cloud Cobra invasion fleet. The CWS Nicholas Kerensky -- originally the SLS Indiana -- served Clan Wolf across centuries of operations before being destroyed above Skye in July 3074 by Word of Blake nuclear weapons, fighting to the last and claiming a Blakist vessel as it broke apart. The CCS Ancestral Home, stranded at Tamaron after a catastrophic KF drive failure, served as a training vessel for decades before its final act of defiance in December 3074: opening a hyperspace field that engulfed half of the Perigard Zalman, a Leviathan Prime-class battleship, destroying both vessels in a spectacular sacrifice. The CJF Falcon's Nest was destroyed in 3073 by nuclear SDS missiles after disabling multiple warships during Operation Ice Storm. The CSR Mountbatten was consumed in the bioweapon horror at Galedon V in 3069. The CSJ Veiled Huntress served as the Smoke Jaguar flagship during the Turtle Bay massacre and throughout the Clan Invasion before being captured and scuttled during Operation BULLDOG. No Texas-class vessels are known to survive.</p>
</deployment>

<history>
<p>The Texas-class battleship was born from the SLDF's painful recognition that its aging Monsoon-class battleships, the backbone of the fleet since the twenty-fourth century, were being consistently outperformed by the navies of member states. In 2616, Krester Ship Construction received the contract for a new capital warship that would leverage over two centuries of technological advancement. The SLDF specifically demanded superior speed and maneuverability -- qualities Krester had already demonstrated with the acclaimed Kimagure-class pursuit cruiser. The breakthrough came from Panthex YM1 lamellor ferro-carbide armor: nearly 1,800 tons of the revolutionary composite provided protection equivalent to 4,500 tons of conventional plating, freeing enormous mass for the engines and weapons systems that would define the Texas.</p><p>The Texas entered service in 2618 and quickly established itself as the SLDF's premier battleship. Fifty-two were constructed at Krester's sprawling Terra orbital facilities, serving across every numbered fleet as capital ships and flagships. The SLS Nebraska served the Eleventh Fleet until Taurian rebels weaponized a fuel ship that destroyed the battleship during the 2765 Periphery Uprising. When the Amaris Coup erupted in December 2766, the SLS Wales was ambushed at New Earth by twenty Rim Worlds warships; Vice Admiral Rummolo fought off the attackers and led survivors to Freedom Station, later commanding the Ninth Fleet during the liberation of New Earth. An ambitious attempt to convert a Texas hull into an M-6 autonomous Caspar drone warship failed spectacularly when the prototype crashed into Pluto.</p><p>Only seven of fifty-two Texas battleships survived the grinding attrition of the Amaris Civil War and Liberation of Terra to join Kerensky's Exodus fleet in 2784. Two more were lost in the brutal Exodus Civil War. The SLS Prinz Eugen gained infamy for the mutiny of August 2785, when nine ships attempted to return to the Inner Sphere before being suppressed. The SLS Bismark, stored in the Norfolk Boneyard on Strana Mechty with permanent keel damage, was secretly restored by Clan Wolverine for their 2823 exodus under saKhan Trish Ebon and vanished with them, never to be seen again.</p><p>The five surviving Clan Texas vessels received comprehensive refits around 2835, gaining lithium-fusion batteries and mobile HPGs to serve as independent command ships. Each became the treasured flagship of its parent Clan: the CWS Nicholas Kerensky for Clan Wolf, the CJF Falcon's Nest for Jade Falcon, the CCS Ancestral Home for Coyote, the CSR Mountbatten for Snow Raven, and the CSJ Veiled Huntress for Smoke Jaguar. The SLS Perth, which had remained in the Pentagon worlds, was found barely functional at Arcadia during Operation KLONDIKE and surrendered to the Clans.</p><p>The Jihad and Wars of Reaving destroyed every surviving Texas in a cascade of catastrophic losses. The Nicholas Kerensky fell to Word of Blake nuclear weapons above Skye in July 3074. The Ancestral Home sacrificed itself at Tamaron in December 3074, opening a hyperspace field that engulfed half of a Leviathan Prime-class battleship and destroying both vessels. The Falcon's Nest was destroyed by nuclear SDS missiles in 3073. The Mountbatten was consumed in the bioweapon horror at Galedon V in 3069. The Veiled Huntress, which had served as the Smoke Jaguar flagship during the Turtle Bay massacre, was captured and scuttled during Operation BULLDOG. The Prinz Eugen, by then in Clan Burrock hands after being subverted by the Society, was destroyed at Tanis in 3073. The most prolific and storied battleship class of the Star League era left no survivors -- every one of the fifty-two vessels built met violent ends across four centuries of conflict.</p>
</history>

